no-object-constructor.description:
Description

This rule disallows calling theObjectconstructor without an argument.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-object-constructor: "error"*/

Object();

new Object();

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/*eslint no-object-constructor: "error"*/

Object("foo");

const obj = { a: 1, b: 2 };

const isObject = value => value === Object(value);

const createObject = Object => new Object();
